[% META title = "Education and Collaboration" %]
[% PageVersion = 'Bmaster/education.tt,v 0.02 2026/03/17 shanta Exp shanta' %]
[% IF debug_mode == 1 %]
    [% PageVersion %]
[% END %]

<div class="app-container">

    <div class="page-header">
        <h1>Education and Collaboration</h1>
        <p class="page-subtitle">Learn beekeeping with our online, in-yard, and workshop training system.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="content-container">
        <div class="content-primary">

            <div class="app-section">
                <p>We believe in the importance of education in promoting beekeeping and conserving our bee populations. Whether you are just getting started or looking to sharpen advanced skills, our educational resources are here to help.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="app-section">
                <h2>Bee Biology</h2>
                <div class="content-section">
                    <p>Understanding bee biology is the foundation of good beekeeping:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Anatomy and physiology of worker bees, drones, and queens</li>
                        <li>The roles of each caste within the colony</li>
                        <li>The life cycle of a bee — egg, larva, pupa, adult</li>
                        <li>Communication: waggle dance, pheromones, and alarm signals</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="app-section">
                <h2>Diseases and Pests</h2>
                <div class="content-section">
                    <p>Learn to identify, prevent, and treat common bee health threats:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Varroa mites — monitoring techniques and treatment options</li>
                        <li>American Foulbrood and European Foulbrood</li>
                        <li>Nosema and other gut pathogens</li>
                        <li>Small Hive Beetle management</li>
                        <li>Integrated Pest Management (IPM) strategies</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p><a href="/BMaster/beehealth">Bee Health Section</a></p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="app-section">
                <h2>Hive Management</h2>
                <div class="content-section">
                    <p>Develop practical hive management skills:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>How to conduct safe and thorough hive inspections</li>
                        <li>Swarm prevention and management</li>
                        <li>Seasonal management — spring buildup to winter preparation</li>
                        <li>Splitting colonies and making increase</li>
                        <li>Feeding bees — when, why, and how</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p><a href="/Apiary/HiveManagement">Hive Management System</a></p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="app-section">
                <h2>Queen Rearing</h2>
                <div class="content-section">
                    <p>Advanced queen rearing education for those ready to improve their genetic stock:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Queen biology and development timeline</li>
                        <li>Grafting techniques and starter/finisher colony setup</li>
                        <li>Mating nuc management</li>
                        <li>Selecting for desirable traits: gentleness, productivity, hygienic behavior</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p><a href="/Apiary/QueenRearing">Queen Rearing System</a></p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="app-section">
                <h2>Workshops and Courses</h2>
                <div class="content-section">
                    <p>We offer hands-on workshops and structured courses for beginner and experienced beekeepers alike. Sessions are held in the yard and online.</p>
                    <p><a href="/workshop" class="btn btn-primary">Browse Upcoming Workshops</a></p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="page-footer">
                <div class="footer-actions">
                    <a href="/BMaster" class="btn btn-secondary">Back to BMaster Home</a>
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>
    </div>

</div>
